    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Re-engage open deals with Airtable and Discord 24/7\n\n**Pattern:** Reminders & Follow-ups · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nRe-engage open deals with Airtable and Discord 24/7. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual contact sync is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Keep Valid Contacts → Segment Audience → Step 1 — Welcome (Discord) → Wait Before Step 2 → Converted Already? → Step 2 — Value Nudge (Discord) → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to reminders & follow-ups without manual effort\n- Anyone automating contact sync in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Responds in seconds\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Airtable PAT; Discord webhook URL; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "cb64ca73-d4e2-e714-2867-692fff21e051",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "cd99114b-a10c-4f33-571b-b93a90e0fe43",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "23edbe5f-b3ec-a35d-5669-5a48220385b7",
      "name": "⏱ Rate limiting"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your contact sync process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
